# Kconfig for built-in input processors

config ZMK_INPUT_PROCESSOR_SCROLL_SMOOTH
    bool "Scroll Smoothing Input Processor (EMA + deadzone + adaptive gain)"
    default y
    depends on DT_HAS_ZMK_INPUT_PROCESSOR_SCROLL_SMOOTH_ENABLED
    select ZMK_POINTING
    help
      Pre-filter for scroll smoothing.  Sits between zip_xy_to_scroll_mapper
      and scroll_inertia.  Applies:
        1) Deadzone truncation  — zero sub-threshold deltas,
        2) EMA low-pass filter  — α = 0..1000 permille,
        3) Adaptive gain        — scale output by velocity.

      Without this filter, scroll_inertia's internal EMA receives raw
      per-event deltas directly from the scroll mapper, which include
      sensor jitter that can make the arming heuristics unreliable
      (false coasts on micro-flicks or missed coasts on fast ones).

      Parameters are settable via Devicetree on the scroll_smooth node.
